The paper discusses the use of software support for formalizing mathematical content, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) to convert informal knowledge into machine-oriented representations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI or cs.LG sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the development of an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for the semantic TeX (sTeX) format, which involves software engineering (SE) techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.SE sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of object-oriented languages, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.PL sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses best practices for implementing IDEs, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.DL sub-category, which focuses on deep learning and neural networks.
